<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Tools on MCP Toolbox for Databases</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/firestore/tools/</link><description>Recent content in Tools on MCP Toolbox for Databases</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/firestore/tools/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>firestore-add-documents</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/firestore/tools/firestore-add-documents/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/firestore/tools/firestore-add-documents/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about"&gt;About&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;firestore-add-documents&lt;/code&gt; tool allows you to add new documents to a
Firestore collection. It supports all Firestore data types using Firestore&amp;rsquo;s
native JSON format. The tool automatically generates a unique document ID for
each new document.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="compatible-sources"&gt;Compatible Sources&lt;/h2&gt;





&lt;div class="compatibility-section"&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;This tool can be used with the following database sources:&lt;/p&gt;

 &lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Source Name&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 
 
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/firestore/source/"&gt;Firestore Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 

 

 
 
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
 &lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2 id="parameters"&gt;Parameters&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Parameter&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Type&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Required&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;collectionPath&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Yes&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;The path of the collection where the document will be added&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;documentData&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;map&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Yes&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;The data to be added as a document to the given collection. Must use &lt;a href="https://cloud.google.com/firestore/docs/reference/rest/Shared.Types/ArrayValue#Value"&gt;Firestore&amp;rsquo;s native JSON format&lt;/a&gt; with typed values&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;returnData&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;boolean&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;No&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;If set to true, the output will include the data of the created document. Defaults to false to help avoid overloading the context&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;h3 id="data-type-format"&gt;Data Type Format&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The tool requires Firestore&amp;rsquo;s native JSON format for document data. Each field
must be wrapped with its type indicator:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>firestore-delete-documents</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/firestore/tools/firestore-delete-documents/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/firestore/tools/firestore-delete-documents/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about"&gt;About&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;firestore-delete-documents&lt;/code&gt; tool deletes multiple documents from Firestore by
their paths.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;firestore-delete-documents&lt;/code&gt; takes one input parameter &lt;code&gt;documentPaths&lt;/code&gt; which is
an array of document paths to delete. The tool uses Firestore&amp;rsquo;s BulkWriter for
efficient batch deletion and returns the success status for each document.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="compatible-sources"&gt;Compatible Sources&lt;/h2&gt;





&lt;div class="compatibility-section"&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;This tool can be used with the following database sources:&lt;/p&gt;

 &lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Source Name&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 
 
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/firestore/source/"&gt;Firestore Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 

 

 
 
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
 &lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

