 &lt;td&gt;Must be &amp;ldquo;firestore-delete-documents&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;source&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td style="text-align: center"&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td style="text-align: center"&gt;true&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Name of the Firestore source to delete documents from.&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;description&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td style="text-align: center"&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td style="text-align: center"&gt;true&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Description of the tool that is passed to the LLM.&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;</description></item><item><title>firestore-get-documents</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/firestore/tools/firestore-get-documents/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/firestore/tools/firestore-get-documents/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about"&gt;About&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;firestore-get-documents&lt;/code&gt; tool retrieves multiple documents from Firestore by
their paths.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;firestore-get-documents&lt;/code&gt; takes one input parameter &lt;code&gt;documentPaths&lt;/code&gt; which is an
array of document paths, and returns the documents&amp;rsquo; data along with metadata
such as existence status, creation time, update time, and read time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="compatible-sources"&gt;Compatible Sources&lt;/h2&gt;





&lt;div class="compatibility-section"&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;This tool can be used with the following database sources:&lt;/p&gt;

